<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="little-adv">little <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'lɪtl/    美 /'lɪtl/  </p>
<p>(less, least)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[表示否定] 少；几乎没有：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I slept very little last night. 
昨晚我几乎没睡。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-know-think-suspect-imagine-expect-realize">2.★ <strong>[用于know, think, suspect, imagine, expect, realize等动词之前] 一点儿也不：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He little knows what may happen. / Little does he know what may happen. 
他一点儿也不知道可能会发生什么事。</p></div>

<p>注: little作状语置于句首时，句子往往部分倒装，结构为：little + 助动词 / be 动词 / 情态动词 + 主语 + 谓语动词。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Little <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (罗斯在乎) her own safety, though she was in great danger herself.  （2009 陕西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. did Rose care about  </p></div>